image.altText: Newly built homes in a housing estate

props.synopsis: The state's building regulator has been exposed for failing to hold builders to account, prompting the government to replace the VBA with a new regulator with greater powers.

title.children: An independent review into the Victorian Building Authority finds it failed to protect homeowners trying to fix defects

image.altText: Map showing an intersection on Dynon Road and City Link.

props.synopsis: Safety oversights on Victoria's big build have led to one cyclist dying and another being paralysed. Advocates say neither incident should ever have happened.

title.children: 'Completely preventable tragedies': The lives shattered by safety oversights on Victoria's big build

image.altText: A red white and blue helicopter in the blue sky.

props.synopsis: A infant has been transported to the Royal Children's Hospital from a town near Ballarat after being injured by a horse.

title.children: Infant receiving treatment after incident involving horse at pub

image.altText: Commonwealth Games Australia boss Craig Phillips

props.synopsis: Craig Phillips has fired another shot at the Victorian government, claiming Commonwealth Games Australia never had a chance to present the 10-sport version of the event heading to Glasgow.

title.children: Commonwealth Games Australia boss fires latest shot at Victoria, says state could have 'absolutely' hosted streamlined event

image.altText: Muslim students kneel to pray in the atrium at Swinburne University Hawthorn campus.

props.synopsis: Students have been locked out of a Swinburne University campus' prayer room on Islam's main day of worship after a clash over who should lead services.

title.children: 'It makes you feel unwelcome': Prayer room closed after dispute between Muslim students and university

image.altText: A group of dancers smile, standing together with Aboriginal face paint, holding gum leaves.

image.altText: A group of about twenty people dressed all in black with their faces covered.

image.altText: Chadwer smiles in a grainy photo taken during a sport training

props.synopsis: Chadwer Leah, who drowned in Melbourne's Yarra River after he was allegedly chased by two teenagers, has been remembered as a talented footballer and role model with "genuine kindness".

title.children: Chadwer Leah, who drowned in the Yarra River, was a 'bright, joyful young man'

image.altText: Firefighters around a crashed plane with a crumples nose on grassy ground.

title.children: Seaford man, 20, dead and investigation underway after plane crash at Vic aerodrome

image.altText: A generic image of a can of coke zero softdrink

image.altText: A child in front of a pile of rubble.

image.altText: Lidia Thorpe strides down the centre aisle of the great hall wearing a possum skin cloak.

image.altText: A smiling woman wears a thick black headband and floral jacket over a hot pink top

image.altText: A sign for Woolworths on top of another for Coles

image.altText: An image of a computer screen.

image.altText: Amanda Murray-Alston holds her daughter at their local primary school.

image.altText: Household money pic

image.altText: vec volunteers begin vote counting in mildura

image.altText: aerial shot of melbourne showing houses and city skyscrapers

image.altText: A man wearing a sombrero poses with an Australian flag

image.altText: A man wearing a cream blazer and blue tie sits in an armchair with a window behind him as he is interviewed

image.altText: Hezbollah leader Hashem Safieddine

image.altText: Still from CCTV of a woman in a pinkl singlet reaching out to a baby being held by its mother

image.altText: A man at a podium in an empty auditorium.

image.altText: A woman and man with sunglasses.

image.altText: Cameron Wurf touches his watch while running

image.altText: A brown snake rearing up with it's mouth open, on red grassy soil.

image.altText: Bullet holes are seen on the front of a Toyota minibus

image.altText: A wide McDonald's storefront logo including the golden yellow 'M'

image.altText: A man with blond hair wearing a suit looks into the distance
